en_550202_0	The first test train was operated today on Matara – Beliatta Railway Track, under the patronage of Minister Arjuna Ranatunga.It was run to inspect the newly built Matara – Beliatta railway track.
en_550202_1	The Government plans to complete the proposed railway track from Matara to Kataragama in three stages.
en_550202_2	The first phase takes place from Matara to Beliatta, the second phase from Beliatta to Hambantota and the 3rd phase will be constructed from Hambantota to Kataragama.
en_550202_3	The total length of the railway track is 113 kilometers.
en_550202_4	The estimated cost to build the railway tract from Matara to Beliatta is 278.2 million dollars.
en_550202_5	The Chinese Exim Bank provides financial assistance and Central Engineering Bureau supervises the constructions.
en_550202_6	The signal lights system has been installed at present.
en_550202_7	Four main stations and two sub railway stations have been built from Matara to Beliatta.
